@agingade
I would like to take this PR to the next step.
Is there anything I can do?

@masaki-yamakawa 
My worry is abandoning the xml support in near future. If you insist to go with this approach, its fine with me.

One change that could help code maintainability is moving your changes (which is duplicate of the code/logic from CreateMappingPreconditionCheckFunction) to RegionMapping as helper methods and then accessing it from both place. 

E.g.:
if (mapping.getFieldMappings().isEmpty() && mapping.getPdxName != null) {
  mapping.createMappingUsingPdx();
}

@kamilla1201 
Other options myself and @dschneider-pivotal were considering about:
Is this issue very specific to cache loader? in that case, let's check if the value is serializable as part of load, if not then send error response back to the caller. 
@dschneider-pivotal Is it a safe assumption to make, anything we load through the cache-loader needs to be serializable...If not, then we may have to see if its serializable based on the thread/caller ?

@agingade 
Thank you for your comment.
I'll try again.

@boglesby @upthewaterspout , thanks a lot for your comments and preliminary review.
I have created a new PR with all the changes squashed and the name of the command changed to wan-copy region:
https://github.com/apache/geode/pull/6601
